filename = "data/geotagged_climate_tweets.csv"
if os.path.isfile(filename):
    # Load cached filtered data
    df = pd.read_csv(filename, lineterminator="\n")
else:
    # Filter the dataset for tweets that are geotagged
    has_geotag = []
    for filename in tqdm(files):
        with tqdm(total = os.path.getsize(filename)) as pbar:
            with open(filename, "r") as file:
                for line in file:
                    pbar.update(len(line))
                    row = json.loads(line)
                    if row["coordinates"] or row["place"]:
                        has_geotag.append(row)
    print(len(has_geotag))
    df = pd.DataFrame(has_geotag)
    df.to_csv(filename, index=False)

In [20]:
filename = "tweets_by_city.csv"
if os.path.isfile(filename):
    tweets_per_city = pd.read_csv(filename)
else:
    results = []
    for city, n_tweets in tqdm(tweets_by_city.items(), total=len(tweets_by_city)):
        bits = city.split(", ")
        matches = cities[(cities.name == bits[0]) & (cities["country code"] == bits[-1])]
        if len(matches) == 0:
            #print(f"{city} not found")
            pass
        elif len(matches) > 1:
            #print(f"{city} matched {len(matches)}")
            matches = cities[(cities.name == bits[0]) & (cities["admin1 code"] == bits[1]) & (cities["country code"] == bits[-1])]
        if len(matches) == 1:
            pop = matches["population"].iloc[0]
            if pop > 0:
                results.append({
                    "city": city,
                    "population": pop,
                    "n_tweets": n_tweets
                })
    print(f"{len(results)} matched out of {len(tweets_by_city)}")
    tweets_per_city = pd.DataFrame(results)
    tweets_per_city.to_csv("tweets_by_city.csv", index=False)

In [26]:
for country, count in df.country.value_counts().head(10).iteritems():
    print(country, count)
    filtered_df = df[df.country == country]
    all_tweets_monthly = filtered_df.created_at.resample("M").count()
    pos_tweets = filtered_df.created_at[filtered_df["compound"] > 0.05].resample("M").count()
    pos_tweets_pc = pos_tweets / all_tweets_monthly * 100
    neg_tweets = filtered_df.created_at[filtered_df["compound"] < -0.05].resample("M").count()
    neg_tweets_pc = neg_tweets / all_tweets_monthly * 100
    neutral_tweets = filtered_df.created_at[filtered_df["compound"].between(-.05, .05)].resample("M").count()
    neutral_tweets_pc = neutral_tweets / all_tweets_monthly * 100



    title = f"{country} climate twitter ({count} tweets) - tweet sentiment as percentage of all climate tweets - by month"
    pos_tweets_pc.plot(figsize=(15,15), title=title,color="g")
    neg_tweets_pc.plot(color='r')
    neutral_tweets_pc.plot()
    plt.legend(["Positive tweets", "Negative tweets", "Neutral tweets"])
    plt.xlabel("year")
    plt.ylabel("% of tweets per month")
    plt.show()

filtered_df = df[df.country != "United States"]
all_tweets_monthly = filtered_df.created_at.resample("M").count()
pos_tweets = filtered_df.created_at[filtered_df["compound"] > 0.05].resample("M").count()
pos_tweets_pc = pos_tweets / all_tweets_monthly * 100
neg_tweets = filtered_df.created_at[filtered_df["compound"] < -0.05].resample("M").count()
neg_tweets_pc = neg_tweets / all_tweets_monthly * 100
neutral_tweets = filtered_df.created_at[filtered_df["compound"].between(-.05, .05)].resample("M").count()
neutral_tweets_pc = neutral_tweets / all_tweets_monthly * 100
